(5,'Waterfall Poetry','📝','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Sensory','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Access to running water or a fountain','Notebook','Pencil'],ARRAY['Sit together near running water, a fountain, stream or tap.','Listen and describe what you hear, see and feel.','Write or dictate a short poem about the water.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.',NULL,8,false),
(5,'Marble Run Engineering','⚙️','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Cardboard tubes and guttering pieces','Marbles','Water and a container to catch drips'],ARRAY['Design and build a marble run that uses water to carry the marble.','Test each section before connecting the whole run.','Time how long the marble takes to travel the full run.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.','Supervise marbles, choking hazard for younger siblings.',5,false),
(5,'Sink the Ship','⛵','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Tin foil','Penny coins','Tub of water and a recording chart'],ARRAY['Shape tin foil into a boat.','Add pennies one at a time and count how many it holds before sinking.','Try different hull shapes and record which holds the most.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.','Always supervise near water.',8,false),
(5,'Floating and Density Sorting','⚖️','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Tub of water','Selection of household objects','Prediction chart'],ARRAY['Before testing, predict: will each object float or sink?','Drop each object in the water and record the result.','Discuss what floats, what sinks, and why.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.','Always supervise near water.',8,false),
(5,'Water Magnifying Lens','🔍','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Large jar filled with water','Small printed text or objects'],ARRAY['Place a jar of water in front of printed text.','Look through the water and see how it magnifies the print.','Try different objects and record what appears bigger through the water lens.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.',NULL,9,false),
(5,'Cloud in a Jar','☁️','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Jar','Very hot water (adult to handle)','Hairspray and ice cubes'],ARRAY['Adult pours a small amount of very hot water into a jar.','Spray hairspray inside briefly then cover with a plate of ice.','Watch a cloud form inside the jar.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.','Adult must handle the hot water. Keep children at a safe distance during setup.',5,false),
(5,'Rain Painting Collaboration','🎨','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Outdoor','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Large paper','Washable paints','Rain and outdoor space'],ARRAY['Lay large paper outside and let children paint their own section.','Leave in light rain to let the drops blend the colours.','Bring inside and discuss the result together.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.',NULL,7,false),
(5,'Ocean Layer Model','🌊','#4dc3ff','Water Play · Science','Water Play','30–50 min',ARRAY['Clear bottles','Materials representing ocean layers (sand, shells, water, oil)','Labels'],ARRAY['Research the ocean zones: sunlit, twilight, midnight, abyssal.','Layer materials in a clear bottle to represent each zone.','Label each layer and present to the family.'],'4 years, Pre-schooler','Pre-schoolers loved imaginative play. By five they can layer in rules, sequences and longer storylines. Those are early formal learning skills.',NULL,6,false);
